emfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:51:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sick luclin npcs- is there a quest related to it?</span><hr size=1> Hi all-<br><br>While roaming through shadowhaven and a few other zones, I've noticed a decent number of &quot;sick&quot; npcs, including one of the &quot;boss&quot; npcs in shadowhaven.  I've also found a decent number of nodrop/lore fungus bits in various places, and a katta quest that results in a glowing-stein graphic item with 5 charges of cure poison/disease.  So I'm curious- do all these pieces come together somehow, and if so, does anyone have any ideas about how?  Haven't gotten much response from any of the npcs beyond &quot;I don't feel well&quot;, etc...<br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urediofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redi of Qeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 1:45:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sick luclin npcs- is there a quest related to it?</span><hr size=1> I noticed the same thing... no real leads on it.<br><br>There's the sick guard in Katta who's cured by some Tea that's the result of a brewing quest in Shar Vahl. Other than that, I don't know of any way to make the NPCs feel better...<br><br>The Katta guard asks specifiically for tea (he's not sure on the name, but gives you clues about it). No other NPC says anything like &quot;Get me X to make me feel better.&quot; *shrug* Anyone try giving the tea to other folks?<br><br>-Redi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uunnone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unnone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 1:50:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sick luclin npcs- is there a quest related to it?</span><hr size=1> Other things I've noticed:  <br><br>1)  Zimloro, gnome in stuntyville SH, sends you out for antidote ingredients to a person in Shadeweavers thicket.  Person gives you back Antidote Ingredients.  Turn into Zimloro, get faction, xp.<br><br>2)  A certain guard (name not recalled)  gives a quest to go to Tenebrous Mtns to see if his friend is safe.  Gnome near wall of Katta, name not recalled.  Give him note, he mentions he was collecting antidote ingredients for Zimloro as well, but can't get them himself.   He needs vampyre blood.  Give him that, and I don't remember what happens for 100%.  I think he gives you something to take back to Zimloro for him, which results in faction/xp, like the other quest.<br><br>3)  Tried giving mug of purifying tonic to Mother Malaria, or whatever her name is.   *Burrrrrp*   What mug?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>4)  Legionairre in Katta is weak and needs tea from brewer in Shar Vahl.  This quest is not solved yet, afaik.  As usual, part of the quest is bugged, destroying an item thats a pain in the butt to get and which should be reusable, like a smithy hammer is.  Except, you can buy a smithy hammer, and don't have to spend 10 hours tracking down 20 no drop leaves from stuff in the newbie ground.<br><br>Things I am thinking about doing, but wondering if someone else has done....<br><br>--- Haven't tried giving antidote ingredients to person other than Zimloro.<br><br>----Haven't given mug to the sick gnome.<br><br>----Haven't given the mug to zimloro.  <br><br>---Haven't mentioned Zimloro to the mug of tonic maker.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 2:52:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sick luclin npcs- is there a quest related to it?</span><hr size=1> Hello again-<br>There's a strange temple-type area in dawnshroud peaks, in the SE corner of the zone, not far from grieg's, that is in fested with mushrooms.  Several different types drop various types of lore/nodrop items that are... mushroom-ie.  There's also a smugglers camp near there (just a bit north) with a &quot;sick&quot; npc in it, but I wasn't able to get anything out of it (i.e. no bracketed text, or response to obvious queries, etc.).<br><br>Will keep looking/asking...<br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uunnone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unnone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:03:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sick luclin npcs- is there a quest related to it?</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah.  Actually, there are a couple sick npcs in Dawnshroud, if I remember correctly.  One is near Sanctus seru, and another is near Maidens Eye.<br><br>Hrmmmm.  we are getting an impressive amount of sick people in luclin.  Wonder if we can get the number up to ten (10 silver links to Vex Thal.....) They don't seem to be scattered across luclin, tho.<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urediofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redi of Qeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:07:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> DSP</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the sick woman in DSP is a courier... someone on the other end of the zone is wondering where her message is. She'll trust you to deliver it, if you give her a certain type of mushroom.<br><br>I've tried giving her a few types, no results. *shrug*<br><br>-Redi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxitix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xitix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:15:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DSP</span><hr size=1> Whole pile of sick people in Echo Caverns as well.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaleficsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maleficSZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:24:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i know why they are sick</span><hr size=1> seizures from those flashing lights caused by bsp holes near zonelines...you know how you sit near a zoneline or corner sometime and there are just random flashing lights seen by everyone in the area, yup...chinese robot seizure power! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvopiululant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vopi Ululant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:25:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DSP</span><hr size=1> It's all them damn Norrathians, they brought up the freaking PLAQUE!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umendan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mendan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:53:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DSP</span><hr size=1> The quest involving the legionaire in Katta looking for tea has been solved for awhile, you can read the details for it <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/quests/luclin_gravelpittea.htm">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxilithtvyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xilith Tvyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.neriak.com/rune4.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 4:36:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DSP</span><hr size=1> The Plaque?  Dear God no!<br><br>Has anyone tried giving them a toothbrush? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=natal>natal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 4:07:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> zimloro</span><hr size=1> I am intrigued <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  What specifically do these characters give you to return to zimloro? I haven't had a chance to run over and check it out myself (stuck in the xp grind <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), are they sorts of things which might be brewed or combined in alchemy? It would be kind of neat if VI placed a series of apparent faction quests to disguise and underlying real quest based on high level brewing or alchemy skill. Make you go and work at it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uessagare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Essagare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 2:01:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: zimloro</span><hr size=1> Ahhh! Is THAT where Zimloro can be found? I got the &quot;antidote&quot; early after Luclin came out and have never been able to find Zimloro to give it to him. The antidote is given by a guy (human I think) in Shadeweaver's Thicket. Go right from the entrance to Shar Vahl (north). Keep the wall on your right and run past the bank, about another two hundred yards, and he is between some rocks. Sorry I can't remember his name, but maybe I will check later and post it, plus loc. <br><br>Essagare Eldertree<br>Heirophant<br>The Rathe<br>El'lar Dobluth<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaynan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daynan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.flagaustnat.asn.au/images/flagcurrent.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 9:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4070.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   